'Guardians of critical Bluetooth beacons' metaphorically refers to users who have been involved in high-priority BLE events, which are essential for the core functionality of Bluetooth systems and categorized under a specific critical category; these users are crucial for maintaining the system’s integrity. ;
Category ID 1 represents the highest level of priority in BLE events, indicating they are essential for the operational efficiency and security of Bluetooth systems. ;
'bf_flag = Y' indicates that the event is mandatory for ensuring the proper functioning of Bluetooth Core functionalities. ;
The user's involvement with these events is tracked through their user ID in the BLE event logs. ;
The end goal is to identify these key users to ensure they are informed and ready to address any issues related to these critical events.

sql:
SELECT DISTINCT b.device_id
FROM ble_events b
INNER JOIN notifications n ON b.event_id = n.event_id;

SELECT category_id
FROM event_monitoring
WHERE event_id = 0 AND threshold > 10;

SELECT device_id, COUNT(DISTINCT event_id) AS unique_events
FROM ble_events
GROUP BY device_id;

SELECT event_id
FROM event_monitoring
WHERE threshold < (SELECT AVG(threshold) FROM event_monitoring);

SELECT timestamp 
FROM event_logs 
WHERE details LIKE '%Advertising report received%' AND device_id = 'DeviceB';

SELECT event_id, category_id, COUNT(*) AS total_logs
FROM event_logs
GROUP BY event_id, category_id;
